Please see the swig tutorial on how to build this: http://www.swig.org/tutorial.html

I don't know my Perl foreign-function interface so I couldn't get this to work, but then I haven't tried hard if at all.

Roughly, it should be as follows:

1)   unix % swig -perl5 swig.i

To generate the files swig_wrap.c and libprimer3.pm.

2) Add swig_wrap to the libprimer build procedure, somewhere, maybe even add these line to project Makefile
   BINDING_WRAP=swig_wrap.o
   BINGING_ARGS=`perl -MExtUtils::Embed -e ccopts`

   then

   unix % gcc -c $(LIBPRIMER) swig_wrap.c \
        `perl -MExtUtils::Embed -e ccopts`
 unix % ld -G $(LIBPRIMEROBJECTS) example_wrap.o -o libprimer3.so

3) You can then use it from perl:
 
    unix % perl
    use libprimer3;
    my $primer = primer3_create ();
  
    etc.

